 day.<br><br>2.  You may not post for 2 FG raids at once.  You must wait til your first FG raid is over then post again for another raid.<br><br>3.  You must post at least 12 hours in advance, this avoids conflicts when people come and look at the boards and see that FG's are not reserved and then form up a raid without posting a reservation.<br><br><br>Please post the header like this:<br><br>Fire giants -- (guild) (date) (time)<br><br>Simple and effective...thanks for your help.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvumil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vumil</A> at: 3/30/01 12:38:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>Slacker Shaman</font></span><br>  Posts: 1254<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/25/01 10:43:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FIRE GIANT RESERVATIONS -- READ.ME</span><hr size=1> Previously posted by Delsonora:<br><br>Ever since the vote on FGs that this board conducted a few months back, there have been discussions about what that vote really meant, how valid FG reservations were, and Ragefire.<br><br>Back then, many of the board users came together, from both sides of the issues and realized that a compromise needed to be made. The issue isn't black and white. <br><br>For those of you who are unaware of what the issues associated with the Fire Giants being made reservable, here they are.<br><br>* Fire Giants are a good learning ground for younger players (sub level 50 mostly).<br>* Fire Giants have a relatively quick re-spawn time for large mobs.<br>* Fire Giants have relatively decent loot for sub 50 and over 50 players.<br><br>However<br><br>* Fire Giants block the entry to Ragefire, which is a FCFS non reservable mob on Brell for the cleric epic quest.<br><br>The problem: People on this board are reserving Fire Giants, not for any of the above reasons, but only to block access from others to Ragefire, which again is a non reservable mob.<br><br>Several guilds have indicated that they will no longer observe fFire Giant reservations unless a compromise is made. <br><br>Here is the compromise we are making.<br><br>We are asking everyone who uses this board and calendar to respect Fire Giant reservations. 90% of the time when Fire Giants are up, Ragefire is not up. The 10% (or less) of the time when Ragefire is up, we are asking Fire Giant crews to respect Ragefire Raiders. But because people have abused the system, signing up for Fire Giants when all they really want to kill is Ragefire, our only choice is to say that Fire Giants are FCFS *while* Ragefire is up. That should only end up to be about 2 - 4 times per week on Brell. The remaining 28-30 spawns of Fire Giants should be allowed to be conducted as scheduled on the board.<br><br>So, a quick review.<br><br>1. We are asking people *not* to reserve Fire Giants simply because they want a crack at Ragefire. We will delete posts in the FG reservations forum which indicate people are reserving Ragefire.<br><br>2. We are asking that the users of the board accept that Fire Giants are FCFS *while* Ragefire is up. People who need to get to Ragefire, which is a non reservable mob can't if they can't kill the FGs which lead to him.<br><br>3. We are asking that the users of this board work with Fire Giant raiders to come up with acceptable solutions if there is conflict, and for Ragefire raiders to respect FG schedules when Ragefire is *not* up.<br><br>This is a difficult issue that was handed to the mods with the outcome of this Fire Giant vote. The only way for FGs to be reserved is if everyone works together and compromises a little bit.<br><br>This is the best we could come up with. I am sure people will be unhappy, but it is a compromise we think has beneficial elements to everyone involved.<br><br>Thanks guys<br><br>Delsonora <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A> at: 6/25/01 11:43:29 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>Slacker Shaman</font></span><br>  Posts: 1255<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/25/01 10:51:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FIRE GIANT RESERVATIONS -- READ.ME  UPDATED</span><hr size=1> Well its been an &quot;unwritten rule&quot; (I was told it was written at one time as well) but here it is in writing since some people have requested that it be put in writing:<br><br>Nagafen raid crews have priority to kill Fire Giants when clearing to get to Nagafen.  Nagafen raiders have a 48 hour period in which they must kill Nagafen.  They do not have the option of rescheduling their raid whereas the Fire Giant raiders can.   It is recommended that both leaders work out an agreement but when it can't be worked out the Nagafen raid has rights to clear the Fire Giants to get to Nagafen.<br><br>We can not have Fire Giant raiders blocking Nagafen on the two days that Nagafen raiders have to take him down.   <p><table><tr><td><a href="http://members.aol.com/mysticdominion/jaradisart.jpg" border=0><img src="http://members.aol.com/mysticdominion/jaradisartsmall.jpg"></a></td><td><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=View&Profile=0&Id=60309">J